🌐 Coursera Automation Framework

⚡ Built with Playwright + TypeScript | Designed for Scalability & Precision

---

✨ About the Project

This is a robust, scalable test automation framework developed using Playwright with TypeScript to simulate real-world user interactions on the Coursera platform.

💡 The framework is designed with a focus on:

- Clean architecture
- Maintainability
- Reusability
- Real-world test scenarios

---

🎯 What Makes This Project Special?

🔹 Industry-standard Page Object Model (POM)
🔹 Separate Locator Management System
🔹 Integrated Allure Reporting for deep insights
🔹 Built-in Retry & Debugging Mechanisms
🔹 Data-driven testing using JSON
🔹 Modular and scalable folder structure

---

🧠 Architecture Overview

        Tests Layer
            ↓
        Pages Layer
            ↓
       Locators Layer
            ↓
        Utilities Layer

💡 Each layer is independent, making the framework easy to maintain and extend.

---

📁 Project Structure

Major_Project/
│
├── tests/                # Test scenarios
├── Pages/                # Page classes (POM)
├── Locators/             # Element selectors
├── utils/                # Test data & helpers
├── allure-results/       # Raw execution data
├── allure-report/        # Detailed reports
├── playwright-report/    # HTML report
├── screenshots/          # Failure evidence
├── test-results/         # Execution artifacts
├── playwright.config.ts  # Central configuration
├── package.json          # Dependencies

---

🚀 Key Capabilities

🔍 Smart Search Automation

- Automates course search
- Applies filters dynamically
- Extracts structured course data

📊 Dynamic Data Extraction

- Retrieves available filters
- Counts categories like Language & Level

🧪 Intelligent Form Validation

- Validates error handling for invalid inputs
- Verifies successful submissions
- Captures evidence for both scenarios

---

⚙️ Execution Workflow

1. Initialize configuration (playwright.config.ts)
2. Launch browser instance
3. Execute test cases from /tests
4. Interact via Page Objects
5. Fetch locators from /Locators
6. Capture results, screenshots & traces
7. Generate reports

---

▶️ Running the Framework

npx playwright test

---

📊 Reporting System

📄 HTML Report

npx playwright show-report

📊 Allure Report

npx allure generate allure-results --clean -o allure-report
npx allure open allure-report

💡 Allure provides:

- Step-level insights
- Execution timeline
- Visual analytics

---

🔁 Reliability Features

- 🔄 Automatic retries (2 times)
- 📷 Screenshot capture on failure
- 🎥 Video recording enabled
- 🧵 Trace viewer for debugging

---

🧩 Design Principles

🔹 Separation of Concerns

Each component (Tests, Pages, Locators) is isolated

🔹 Reusability

Common logic is centralized

🔹 Scalability

New tests can be added without breaking existing ones

---

📦 Dependencies

- "@playwright/test" – Core automation engine
- "allure-playwright" – Reporting integration
- "luxon" – Date/time handling

---

💡 Why Playwright?

- Fast execution 🚀
- Auto-waiting features ⏳
- Cross-browser support 🌐
- Powerful debugging tools 🔍

